00:00:00.768 --> 00:00:01.536
<b>When you carry,</b>

00:00:01.792 --> 00:00:04.792
<b>adjusting one hand </b>
<b>to hold the near corner of the load, </b>

00:00:04.793 --> 00:00:07.169
<b>positions one elbow closer to your side. </b>

00:00:07.424 --> 00:00:10.240
<b>This reduces the stress on your shoulders and spine.</b>

00:00:11.008 --> 00:00:12.544
<b>With your hands in this position</b>

00:00:13.056 --> 00:00:15.872
<b>it is easy to shift the load and open a triangle of vision.  </b>

00:00:16.384 --> 00:00:18.176
<b>This enables you to see your next step.</b>

00:00:18.944 --> 00:00:19.456
<b>Finally, </b>

00:00:19.712 --> 00:00:23.040
<b>this hand position makes it easier to set the corner of the load down;</b>

00:00:23.296 --> 00:00:24.832
<b>then slide the load where you want it.</b>

